The paper deals with the performance analysis of a device-to-device (D2D) network, which is a subfield of computer networks and falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of mathematical models and statistical analysis, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and statistical theory (cs.ST). The paper also discusses the optimization of network performance, which can be categorized under the subfield of optimization and control (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of probability theory and stochastic processes, which are common in the subfields of machine learning (cs.MA) and probability (cs.PF).
